</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FB3B369AE4416E1B4FC8FA4AFEB7F941" blockId="100.[151,1436,1389,1666]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis id="C9F0EA88E4416E1B4FC8FA4AFEADFA0D" box="[199,283,1461,1486]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Female</emphasis>
—Unknown. 
<emphasis id="C9F0EA88E4416E1B4EBBFA4AFDBFFA0E" box="[436,521,1461,1486]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
Male 
<emphasis id="C9F0EA88E4416E1B4EE2FA49FDBFFA0E" bold="true" box="[493,521,1462,1485]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">—</emphasis>
</emphasis>
Length ca 
<quantity id="3C7C9B7FE4416E1B4D8EFA4AFD64FA0E" box="[641,722,1461,1486]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
, head and mesosoma black, metasoma black. 
<emphasis id="C9F0EA88E4416E1B4BD7FA4AFA9BFA0D" box="[1240,1325,1461,1486]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Head—</emphasis>
Face with appressed, yellow hair; F1–2, length about equal to width; F3–11, length greater than length; malar space polished length about 0.5 x width; gena with long yellow hair. 
<emphasis id="C9F0EA88E4416E1B4DF8FA01FC31F9D6" box="[759,903,1534,1557]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<taxonomicName id="3C844D19E4416E1B4DF8FA01FCDDF9D6" box="[759,875,1534,1557]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mesosoma</taxonomicName>
—
</emphasis>
Legs orange, simple; propodeal triangle mostly smooth and simple with no transverse carina delimiting the base. 
<emphasis id="C9F0EA88E4416E1B4C60F9DDFC4BF9FA" box="[879,1021,1570,1593]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Metasoma—</emphasis>
Integument with long, orange shaggy hair; no hair bands; gradulus not defined; S4–5 with apical sternal fringes. Hidden sterna and genitalia not available for study.
</paragraph>
